quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  19,1,Kaaf Haa Yaa Aiin Saad
  19,2,A mention of the mercy of your Lord on His servant Zechariah
  19,3,"when he prayed to his Lord, praying secretly"
  19,4,"He said, \"My Lord! my bones have become weak and my head is shining with grey hair and I have never been unsuccessful in my prayer to you, my Lord"
  19,5,And I fear my heirs after me and my wife is barren. So grant me from Yourself a heir
  19,6,"who should inherit me and inherit from the family of Jacob, and make him, O my Lord! pleasing"
  19,7,"(It was said), “O Zechariah! We give you the good news of a son whose name will be John. We did not assign (this) name to anyone before"
  19,8,"He said, \"My Lord! how shall I have a son when my wife is barren and I have reached the extreme degree of old age"
  19,9,"It was said, \"(It will be) like that, your Lord says it is easy for Me and I had created you before when you were nothing"
  19,10,"He said, \"My Lord! make for me a sign,\" He said, \"Your sign is that you will not speak to mankind for three nights (though) in sound health"
  19,11,So he came out to his people from the sanctuary then communicated to them by signs that they should glorify (God) morning and evening
  19,12,"O John ! hold the book with strength.\" And We gave him wisdom (in) childhood (itself)"
  19,13,"and compassion from Us and purity, and he was one who guarded (against evil)"
  19,14,"and dutiful to his parents and he was not compelling (rebellious), disobedient"
  19,15,And peace be on him on the day he was born and the day he dies and the day he will be raised alive